Back to top

Transactions Admin

This section covers all endpoints that a site administrator could use to view information about their customers and manage orders in FoxCommerce. All endpoints in this section require the user to be authenticated as an administrator.

Customers ¶

Customer represents an account of person who buys products in the store.

Customer  ¶

View
GET/v1/customers/{id}

Example URI

GET /v1/customers/1
URI Parameters
HideShow
id
number (required) Example: 1

Customer ID.

Response  200

  ]
}

Enable / Disable
POST/v1/customers/{id}/disable

Example URI

POST /v1/customers/1/disable
URI Parameters
HideShow
id
number (required) Example: 1
Request
HideShow
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "disabled": false
}
Schema
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
  "type": "object",

Create
POST/v1/orders

Creates a cart for an existing customer (or guest account) when customerId given or creates a cart along with a new guest account when email is given.

Shipping Method  ¶

Shipping methods are used to describe the ways that the contents of a cart can transported to the customer. All actions that occur against this set of endpoints modify which shipping method is used by the cart.

List
GET/v1/orders/shipping-methods

Example URI

GET /v1/orders/shipping-methods
Response  200
HideShow
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "UPS Ground",
    "price": 10,
    "isEnabled": true
  }
]
Schema
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
  "type": "array"
}

Update
PATCH/v1/orders/{refNum}/shipping-methods

Changes the shipping method to a cart.

Example URI

PATCH /v1/orders/1/shipping-methods

HideShow

string (required) Example: 1

Delete

Removes the shipping method from the cart.

string (required) Example: 1

Gift Cards ¶

Gift Card is a payment method with unique code, not related to any customer account.

Gift Card  ¶

View
GET/v1/gift-cards/{code}

GET /v1/gift-cards/ABC-123

  "required": [

    "availableBalance"
  ]
}

Create
POST/v1/gift-cards

Creates a GiftCard with CsrAppeasement type, which is only supported at this endpoint. If quantity parameter is provided in payload, multiple GiftCard will be generated.

Example URI

Convert to StoreCredit
POST/v1/gift-cards/{code}/convert/{customerId}

Converts GiftCard to specified customers Store Credit if its active and has no open adjustments.

Promotions ¶

Promotions are the basis of discounts, they contain offer and qualifier objects. A promotion can be auto-applied or can be tied to a coupon the customer must enter in order for the promotion to be applied.

Promotions  ¶

Create
POST/v1/promotions/{context}

Example URI

POST /v1/promotions/default
URI Parameters
HideShow
context
string (required) Example: default

The context in which the promotion will be viewable.

Request
HideShow
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "applyType": "auto",

    "attributes": "<json>",
    "discounts": [

        "attributes": "<json>"
      }
    ]
  },
  "shadow": {
    "attributes": "<json>",
    "discounts": [

        "attributes": "<json>"
      }
    ]
  }
}

Notes ¶

Notes represent additional text data added by store admins to orders, returns and gift cards, viewable by other store admins.
